'''Christopher Bell''' (born 18 November 1957) is a British businessman who was Chief Executive Officer of [[Ladbrokes Coral|Ladbrokes]] from 2006 until May 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ladbrokes chief executive Chris Bell in surprise departure after 20 years|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/retailandconsumer/6972263/Ladbrokes-chief-executive-Chris-Bell-in-surprise-departure-after-20-years.html|website=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|accessdate=13 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Former Ladbrokes CEO Christopher Bell joins Rank board|url=http://www.gamingintelligence.com/people/31709-former-ladbrokes-ceo-christopher-bell-joins-rank-board|website=Gaming Intelligence|accessdate=13 April 2018}}</ref>

He was educated at [[Mexborough Academy|Mexborough Grammar School]] and [[University of Wolverhampton|Wolverhampton Polytechnic]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Big shot of the week: Even a top bookie has to bow to the law of averages|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/big-shot-of-the-week-even-a-top-bookie-has-to-bow-to-the-law-of-averages-r7ntd6hnr5f|website=[[The Times]]|accessdate=13 April 2018}}</ref> He was previously Chairman of [[Game (retailer)|Game]] until March 2012, and is a former Chairman of [[Business in Sport and Leisure]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Executive Profile: Christopher Bell|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=1054321&privcapId=387255|website=[[Bloomberg L.P.]]|accessdate=13 April 2018}}</ref> He is currently Chairman of [[OnTheMarket]], [[Team17]], Techfinancials Inc and XL Media plc.<ref>{{cite web|title=City Moves for 3 November 2017 - who's switching jobs at Sarasin & Partners, OnTheMarket and Hambro Perks?|url=http://www.cityam.com/275066/city-moves-3-november-2017-whos-switching-jobs-sarasin|website=[[City A.M.]]|accessdate=13 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Board of Directors |url=https://www.team17group.com/about-us/board-of-directors/ |website=[[Team17]] |accessdate=21 June 2018}}</ref>

