{{Infobox officeholder | name = Nicanor Restrepo Giraldo | office = [[List of mayors of Medellín|Mayor of Medellín]] | predecessor = [[Henrique Gaviria]] | successor = [[Alfonso Vieira Jaramillo]] | termend = January 1925 | termstart = February 1924 | office2 = [[List of mayors of Medellín|Mayor of Medellín]] | predecessor2 = [[Antonio M. Ramírez]] | successor2 = [[Jesús Escobar (politician)|Jesús Escobar]] | termend2 = September 1908 | termstart2 = March 1904 | office1 = Governor of [[Jericó Department|Jericó]] | predecessor1 = ''Position established'' | termend1 = 1909 | termstart1 = 1908 | birth_date = June 1871 | birth_place = [[Medellín]], [[Antioquia Department|Antioquia]], [[Colombia]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1938|05|19|1871|06}} | death_place = [[Medellín]], [[Antioquia Department|Antioquia]], [[Colombia]] | spouse = Ana Jesús Correa Correa | occupation = Businessman; politician }}
'''Nicanor Restrepo Giraldo''' (June 1871 – 19 May 1938) was a [[Colombia|Colombian]] businessman and politician who served as Mayor of [[Medellín]] from 1904 to 1908, and later from 1924 to 1925. He also served as Governor of the now-defunct [[Jericó Department|Department of Jericó]] from 1908 to 1909.
== Biography == Restrepo Giraldo was born in June 1871 in [[Medellín]], [[Colombia]], to parents Lisandro Restrepo Arango and Dolores Giraldo Gómez.
