{{Infobox person |name = Nicholas X. Notias |image = Notias.jpg |birth_date = 1966 |birth_place = New York, U.S.A. |residence = [[Manhattan]], NYC |nationality = [[Greek American]] |parents = Harry N. Notias, Phyllis Thravalos |education = [[Master of Business Administration]] [[Fordham University]] – [[Bachelor of Arts]] [[Fordham University]] |occupation = [[Businessman]] – [[Shipping]] – [[Real estate]] |home_town = [[Chios]], [[Greece]] }}
'''Nicholas X. Notias''' ({{lang-el|Νικόλαος Χ. Νοτιάς}}; born 1966), is a [[Greek American]] [[businessman]], [[ship-owner]] and [[ship-manager]], owner of Seabridge Chartering LLC located in Wall Street, [[Vice President]] and [[Chief operating officer|Director of Operations]] of Independence Maritime Agency Inc. and Trojan Maritime Inc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maritime-network.net/shipping-directory/shipping-company,trojan-maritime-inc,14239.htm |title=Trojan maritime inc., Shipping companies, Greece &#124; Shipping Directory – World |publisher=Maritime Network |date= |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> He's also a large [[shareholder]] of the [[real estate]] Notias Constructions Company, [[Chief operating officer|Director of Operations]] of Cardiff Holdings Inc., [[Chief operating officer|Director of Operations]] of Liverpool Holdings Inc., and until June 2013, the major shareholder and [[Vice President]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=2996 |title=AEKfc : The Club : Board of Directors |publisher=AEK F.C. Official Web Site |date= |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> of the famous Greek football club [[AEK Athens]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espressonews.gr/default.asp?pid=79&catid=42&artID=821704 |script-title=el:Φυσάει Νοτιάς στα πανιά της ΑΕΚ |publisher=Espresso News |date=2008-08-31 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-08-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721081403/http://www.espressonews.gr/default.asp?pid=79&catid=42&artID=821704 |archivedate=2011-07-21 |df= }}</ref>
== Family and education == Son of the late Harry N. Notias and Phyllis Thravalos, he had a beloved sister named Irene.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/nytimes/obituary.aspx?pid=168315328 |title=Paid Notice: Deaths : NOTIAS, IRENE |work=The New York Times |date=2013-12-03 |accessdate=2013-12-19}}</ref> His father, "Captain Harry"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B03E3DF163AF932A05752C0A9619C8B63 |title=Paid Notice: Deaths : NOTIAS, HARRY N. |work=The New York Times |date=2007-01-31 |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> as he was fondly known, immigrated in the early 1940s from the Greek island [[Chios]] and became a US citizen. He was a selfmade man who achieved the American dream. He came from a close-knit family of modest means, became a [[Captain (nautical)|Captain]] in the [[U.S. Maritime Service]] and later founded a successful [[shipping]] [[business]], Independence Maritime Agency Inc., with offices in New York and Greece. Nicholas followed his father roots and values, and after graduating with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] (1988) and a [[Master of Business Administration]] (1990) from [[Fordham University]], took over the family business. Nikos Notias is married to Maria C. Los, Deputy Chairman of Chritie's Auction Houses.
== Shipping and business success == Nikos Notias has extensive experience in the day to day commercial operations of dry-bulk carriers ([[handymax]] / [[panamax]]), time/voyage [[charters]], charter party disputes, laytime issues, ship S&P, [[insurance]] placement (H&M, P&I, War Risk), claims experience in [[cargo]], P/A & G/A, technical experience in ship repairs and repair contracts, paint coatings and dry-dockings. Yachting industry experience for motor yachts including brokerage, construction and transport.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.smany.org/sma/memberRoster.html |title=Society Of Maritime Arbitrators Roster Of Members : NOTIAS, Nicholas X. |publisher=Society Of Maritime Arbitrators Inc. |date= |accessdate=2010-07-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100119055120/http://www.smany.org/sma/memberRoster.html |archivedate=2010-01-19 |df= }}</ref> Also expert in chartering of a fleet of dry [[bulk carrier]]s engaged in the [[international]] [[transport]] of bulk commodities world wide.
== Professional associations == * [[Maritime Arbitrator]] – Society of Maritime Arbitrators, Inc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.best-maritime-crewing.info/catalogue_companies_list/company_source_32076_5.html |title=Society of Maritime Arbitrators Inc (ID: 32076) : NOTIAS, Nicholas X. |publisher=Best-maritime-crewing.info |date= |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> – [[New York City]] (2001–Present) * Supporting Member of [[Liaison Committee]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lmaa.org.uk/panels-SMLC.aspx |title=The LMAA : The Supporting Members Liaison Committee |publisher=The London Maritime Arbitrators Association |date= |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> – The London [[Maritime Arbitrators Association]] (2003 – Present) * Chairman USA [[Advisory Committee]] – [[Lloyd’s Register]] North America (Member 1995 – Present: Chairman 2004–Present) * Member – [[American Bureau of Shipping]] – (1995 – Present)
== AEK Athens involvement == [[File:Nik8.jpg|thumb|130px|Notias at OACA]] With AEK struggling terribly in corruption and the prospect of relegation to the fourth division looming, [[Demis Nikolaidis]] (ex club charismatic player) supported by the majority of AEK fans, established a [[consortium]] of businessmen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capital.gr/news.asp?Details=554393 |script-title=el:ΠΑΕ με "άρωμα θάλασσας" |publisher=Capital |date=2008-08-11 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-08-11}}</ref> such as [[Polys V. Hajioannou]], [[Petros Pappas]] and [[Takis Kanellopoulos (businessman)|Takis Kanellopoulos]], who convinced Nikos Notias to participate in the project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tovima.gr/default.asp?pid=2&artid=190905&ct=5&dt=07/09/2008 |script-title=el:Νίκος Νοτιάς |publisher=To Bhma Online |date=2008-09-07 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> The approach was made by Ghikas Goumas, grandson of the late Nikos Goumas (former President of the Club). At the first contact, which was held in [[New York City]], Nikos Notias was convinced that the operators had pure purposes, and a great vision for the clubs regeneration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sport24.yooblog.gr/2008/09/05/441/ |script-title=el:Γλυκός Νοτιάς |publisher=SPORT 24 |date=2008-09-05 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-07-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120714114336/http://sport24.yooblog.gr/2008/09/05/441/ |archivedate=2012-07-14 |df= }}</ref> Small doubts initially led Notias to take a small percentage of shares (about 8%) but he changed his mind quickly, when he realized that the fans totally backed-up the effort and gradually, over a period of three and a half years, he became the major holder of the shares, reaching 35%. His financial assistance<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enet.gr/?i=news.el.article&id=37287 |script-title=el:Μόνο ο Νοτιάς βάζει λεφτά! |publisher=Ελευθεροτυπία Online |date=2009-04-22 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-08-11}}</ref> to the club amounts to 18 million [[euros]] but the largest and most expected [[project]] of Nikos Notias, remains the clubs Sports Center<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tanea.gr/default.asp?pid=2&ct=5&artid=85211 |script-title=el:"Απογειώνεται" από τα Σπάτα |publisher=TA NEA Online |date=2008-09-04 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-08-11}}</ref> which will cost over 25 million [[euros]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aek365.gr/article.php?id=56339 |script-title=el:Χλιδή το προπονητικό |publisher=Aek365.gr |date=2010-04-21 |language=Greek |accessdate=2010-07-01}}</ref> It will be the biggest project in the modern history of the club and Notias's intention is to name it "Harry Notias" in honour of his father. Among the tremendous economic crisis in Greece and due to the clubs financial problems, AEK Athens in June 2013 declared bankruptcy and was self-relegated to the amateur third division. The Athletic Center of Spata nowadays includes state of the art facilities, three fields (one of them with synthetic turf) for soccer, a fitness and health center with weight-training and fitness rooms, a cryotherapy center and more. Unfortunately, the rest of the project (the clubs Museum, Hotel, Aquatic Center and two more soccer fields) could not be delivered and remained unfinished.
