{{Infobox company | name = OverOps, Inc. | logo = | type = [[Private company]] | traded_as = | foundation = 2011 | location = [[San Francisco, United States]] | former_name = Takipi | revenue = | net_income = | assets = | num_employees = | key_people = Rod Squires ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]]), Tal Weiss (founder) | industry = [[Software analytics]] | products = | owner = Tal Weiss, Iris Shoor,<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/sites/women2/2013/12/23/10-female-founders-to-watch-out-of-israel/ Female founder to watch out of Israel]. Forbes.com</ref><ref>[http://www.geektime.com/2014/01/07/and-the-geeky-goes-to/ The 2013 Geek Award winners]. geektime.com</ref> Niv Steingarten, Chen Harel and Dor Levi | homepage = {{URL|www.overops.com}}}}
'''OverOps''' is a [[software analytics]] company based in San Francisco, CA and Tel Aviv, Israel. The company develops a [[Static program analysis|static]] and [[Dynamic program analysis|dynamic]] code analysis technology to analyze code events in real time. The technology's focus is large-scale [[Java (programming language)|Java]]<ref>[https://weblogs.java.net/blog/editor/archive/2013/11/20/takipi-analyzes-most-popular-code-libraries-java-developers-use-today-also-ruby-and-javascript-de Takipi Analyzes the Most Popular Code Libraries Java Developers]. java.net</ref> and [[Scala (programming language)|Scala]]<ref>[https://typesafe.com/blog/Introducing-Takipi-God-Mode-in-Production-Scala-Code Introduction to Takipi]. typesafe.com</ref> code bases.
== History == OverOps was founded as '''Takipi''' in December 2011. Prior to Takipi, Tal Weiss (CTO) and Iris Shoor (VP Product)<ref>[http://www.geektime.co.il/geek-on-one-iris-shoor/ Geek on one: Iris Shoor, founder Takipi]. geektime.co.il</ref> co-founded VisualTao (acquired by [[Autodesk Inc]] in 2009).<ref>[https://techcrunch.com/2009/12/17/autodesk-acquires-sequoia-backed-software-design-startup-planplatform/ Audodesk acquires sequoia backed software design]. techcrunch.com</ref> In 2012 Takipi received seed investment of $700K by private investors. In 2013 Takipi received $4.5 million in venture capital from [[Menlo Ventures]].<ref>[http://www.globes.co.il/serveen/globes/docview.asp?did=1000899427 Server debugging co Takipi raises $4.5M]. globes.co.il</ref>
On April 20, 2016, it was announced that Takipi raised $15 million in a funding round led by [[Lightspeed Ventures]].<ref>[http://fortune.com/2016/04/20/term-sheet-wednesday-april-20/]. forbes.com</ref>
Takipi was renamed OverOps on August 25, 2016 to reflect a greater emphasis on services that support [[DevOps]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.takipi.com/overops-rebrand/ |title=Takipi is Now OverOps |date=August 25, 2016 |first=Tal |last=Weiss |work=OverOps Blog |accessdate=August 30, 2016}}</ref>
On April 26, 2017, it was announced that OverOps raised $30 million in series C round led by [[Lightspeed Ventures]], with participation from [[Menlo Ventures]].<ref>[https://techcrunch.com/2017/04/26/overops-scores-30-million-led-by-lightspeed-ventures/ OverOps scores $30 million led by Lightspeed Ventures] TechCrunch.com</ref>
Later that year OverOps was named a 2017 Cool Vendor in Performance Analysis By [[Gartner]].<ref>{{cite web|title=OverOps Named a 2017 Cool Vendor in Performance Analysis By Gartner|url=https://blog.takipi.com/overops-named-a-2017-cool-vendor-in-performance-analysis-by-gartner/|website=OverOps Blog|accessdate=1 June 2017}} </ref>
In 2018 the company announced the hiring of Rod Squires as CEO and move of founder Tal Weiss into the role of Chief Technology Officer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Software Analytics Company OverOps Hires Rod Squires as CEO|url=https://www.readitquik.com/news/business-support-solutionsservices/software-analytics-company-overops-hires-rod-squires-as-ceo/|website=ReadITQuik|accessdate=23 March 2018}}</ref>
== Products == OverOps uses a Java agent to perform code analysis and track code changes in real time. Using graph analysis, OverOps maps an application's [[codebase]] and the different connections between variables, methods and classes. When a runtime exception, log error or a performance issue<ref>[https://venturebeat.com/2013/06/03/amazon-web-services-speeds-can-vary-by-up-to-200x-depending-on-region/ Amazon Web Services Speeds Can Vary By Up To 200x Depending On Region]. venturebeat.com</ref> are reported, the code maps are used to record data of variable values, methods, threads and JVMs which led to the errors. OverOps is delivered in a [[software as a service]] (SaaS) model, where the majority of the analysis is performed in the "[[Cloud computing|cloud]]". The software can also be deployed in a hybrid model (where collector and agent are on-prem with analytics in the cloud) or fully on-prem for all components.
